article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 67, Bryant 62
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Will Campbell scored 19 points and Monmouth defeated winless Bryant 67-62 on Saturday night. Campbell was 7 of 12 from the field, including 5 of 8 from 3-point range in the Hawks' fourth-straight win. Campbell's 3-pointer with 2 minutes to go put Monmouth (7-9, 3-1 Northeast Conference) up for good, 64-62. Tied 37-37 at halftime, the Hawks went on an 11-6 run to lead 48-43 on a free throw by Travis Taylor with 16:29 to play. A three-point play by Erik Smith gave the Bulldogs (0-16, 0-4) back the lead, 62-60, with 4:46 left. Dutch Gaily then hit a free throw pulled the Hawks within 62-60 with 3:22 to play. Bryant, which hasn't won since Feb. 17, was outrebounded 34-27, including 11 by Gaitley. Taylor finished with 16 and Justin Sofman had 11 for the Hawks. The Bulldogs were led by Vladyslav Kondratyev with 15 points and Adam Parzych with 14.
